00:17:21.819 --> 00:17:24.619
Is there a way to put confidence intervals on the monitoring metrics?

00:17:24.619 --> 00:17:25.739
Ah, yes.

00:17:25.739 --> 00:17:32.859
So depending on the aggregation, the time aggregation that you use for model monitoring,

00:17:32.859 --> 00:17:35.859
you have a certain number of observations in then.

00:17:35.859 --> 00:17:41.420
And then you can use the, when you have that sort of feedback loop where you have the real

00:17:41.420 --> 00:17:47.579
answer of whatever the prediction should be, depending, let's say in a week, you have

00:17:47.579 --> 00:17:48.699
a thousand examples.

00:17:48.699 --> 00:17:54.859
You can use those thousand examples to estimate exactly a confidence interval on what the,

00:17:54.859 --> 00:18:00.739
or an interval on the metric that you're measuring.

00:18:00.739 --> 00:18:01.739
Thank you.

00:18:01.739 --> 00:18:02.739
Let's thank Julia again.

00:18:02.739 --> 00:18:03.739
Thank you.

